@startuml sequence_company_login
' Sequence Diagram - Company Login
' Purpose: Shows the business workflow from user login (demo credentials) through
' company selection with password to establishment of company-scoped session.
' Participants: Actor (Accountant or Company Owner), LoginPage, AuthContext,
' CompanySelector, CompanyPasswordModal, Auth API, Company DB. Academic documentation.

title Sequence Diagram - Company Login

actor "Company Owner" as User
participant "LoginPage" as LoginPage
participant "AuthContext" as AuthContext
participant "CompanySelector" as CompanySelector
participant "CompanyPasswordModal" as Modal
participant "Auth API" as API
database "Company DB" as DB

== User authentication ==
User -> LoginPage : Enter username and password
LoginPage -> AuthContext : login(username, password)
AuthContext -> AuthContext : Validate (static credentials)
AuthContext -> AuthContext : setAuthenticated(true)
AuthContext -> AuthContext : Persist to localStorage
AuthContext --> LoginPage : success
LoginPage -> User : Redirect to /companies

== Company selection ==
User -> CompanySelector : Select company from list
CompanySelector -> Modal : Open modal (companyId)
Modal -> User : Request company password
User -> Modal : Enter company password
Modal -> API : POST /auth/company/select\n{ company_id, password }

API -> DB : Load Company by id
DB --> API : Company
API -> API : verify_company_password(password, hash)
alt Invalid password
  API --> Modal : 401 Invalid company password
  Modal --> User : Show error
else Valid password
  API -> API : create_company_token(company_id)
  API --> Modal : 200 { access_token, company }
  Modal -> Modal : setCompanyToken(access_token)
  Modal -> CompanySelector : Set company in context
  CompanySelector -> User : Redirect to app (e.g. /financial-items)
end

@enduml
